short_description:
Fully preemptive event-driven real-time operating system for AVR microcontrollers written in assembly language and supporting events, timers, mutexes.

Minimal context switching time @ 8 MHz:
- on mutex release: 37 us;
- on event-flag: 37 us;
- on external interrupt event: 39 us;
- on task blocking: 42 us;
- on timer event: 49 us.

Memory consumption:
- clean OS (kernel + idle-task): 756 bytes Flash + 48 bytes SRAM;
- 8 tasks, timers, events, mutexes – 1312 bytes Flash + 360 bytes SRAM;
- 32 tasks, timers, events, mutexes – 1474 bytes Flash + 1596 bytes SRAM.

For example: uRTOS can drive 5 separate user tasks at ATtiny45.

